Starting with converting from Fahrenheit to degrees Celsius, what information do we need from the user?
  Show the student how to save the input as an integer using the line int tempFahrenheit = scanner.nextInt() if they haven’t learned nextInt() already.
  
Have the student use math operators to convert to degrees Celsius then print the result.
  Checking the result against an online conversion calculator, what do they notice about the result?
  Guide the student towards noticing that since our result is an integer, it always rounds down, resulting in a less accurate answer.

How can we get a more accurate conversion? The student should use casting to convert tempFahrenheit to a double.
  Now let’s say we want to round our answer to the nearest degree. We can cast the answer back to an integer to do so.

Finally the student should perform the operations in reverse to convert from Celsius to Fahrenheit.

Instructor Note: Don't use the methods from java.lang.Math in the solution! Only casting should be used.
  You can also show the student how to use nextDouble() to store the input as a double.



import java.util.Scanner;

class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

    // Get input from user
    System.out.print("Enter a temperature in degrees Farenheit: ");
    int tempFahrenheit = scanner.nextInt();

    // Conversion without casting (less precise)
    int tempCelsiusInt = (tempFahrenheit - 32) * 5 / 9;
    //System.out.println("Temperature in Celsius (int): " + tempCelsiusInt);

    // Conversion with casting
    double tempCelsius = ((double)tempFahrenheit - 32) * 5 / 9;
    System.out.println("Temperature in Celsius: " + tempCelsius);

    // Conversion rounded to the nearest degree
    int nearestDegree = (int) (tempCelsius + 0.5);
    System.out.println("Temperature in Celsius (rounded): " + nearestDegree);

    // Reverse conversion 
    System.out.print("Enter a temperature in degrees Celsius: ");
    int tempCelsius2 = scanner.nextInt();
    double tempFahrenheit2 = ((double)tempCelsius2 * 9 / 5) + 32; 
    int tempFahrenheitRounded = (int) (tempFahrenheit2 + 0.5);
    System.out.println("Temperature in Fahrenheit: " + tempFahrenheit2);
    System.out.println("Temperature in Fahrenheit (rounded): " + tempFahrenheitRounded);

  }
}
